n class=title> BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> Opinions on xp/loot for 49/50 ... either BW or CS?  If not there.. where?<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujadrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 9:19:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> CS.<br>
<br>
Especially if your not KOS.<br>
Great fast Xp, decent PP, and a vendor in the zone.<br>
Its paradise ) <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=2602"><b>Jadrax Darkfire</b></a><br> 
<A HREF="http://www.britlore.co.uk"><IMG SRC="http://www.britlore.co.uk/images/logo/BritLoreT3.gif" 
ALT="Britannic Lore of Tarrew Marr" WIDTH="248" HEIGHT="75" BORDER="0"></A><br><b><a href="http://www.deviantblood.org/cgi-bin/Ultimate.cgi?action=intro&BypassCookie=true"><b>Tarrew Marr</b></a><br> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwolfystyle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfystyle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/xesevoli2000/signature.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 9:51:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> CS is better xp, but BW is better loot because you have the chance of possibly coming across a rare named spawn.<br>
CS is steady, and reasonably safe xp,and nice loot pp wise, but boring as hell after a few days/months/years there. <p>Xesevoli Wolfy<br>
51 Channeler<br>
Elven Royal Guard<br>
Vallon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushinari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shinari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 11:37:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> I would continue with DreadLands.  Easy to solo and very easy to get clarity and sow at North wall.  1 Ice Comet and 1 rend takes the spiders down and you can kill 2 mobs in one round of mana there.  The Drakes suck in Cobalt Scar and I was soloing the Wyverns at 53 but found to many turning green.  Drakes will eat you and Dl is still a great spot because of the other players around for rez, sow, clarity <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I stayed in DL till I was 53.  Mobs got a little tougher to find but I was very comfortable there.<br>
<br>
Shinari <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 4:40:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> Burning woods and Cobalt Scar are great at 49.  I should think that BW would be better overall xp though.  CS can get kinda slow when you have a wizard and dr00d there quad-kiting every mob in the zone and constantly training you with Cobalt drakes.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzukhov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zukhov</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.tripod.co.uk/EQZukhov/Zport.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 5:14:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.tripod.co.uk/EQZukhov/sigg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> CS is very very easy. Kiting the wyverns is virtually risk free if you are on friendly terms with them. They also give no faction hits and don't assist each other.<br>
<br>
If you get problems from the drakes then you can just otter them.<br>
<br>
Something is seriously wrong with this zone, <p>Zukhov Chertava<BR>
Hack and Slash Gamer<BR>
Wizard<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kazzap>Kazzap</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 5:33:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> Although I love BW/CS/DL, the choice for 49 is VERY clear.  Oasis spectres.  One Ice Comet at 49 and they are almost on a death crawl.  Single pulls, fast respawns, and they give amazing exp solo for being such weaklings.<br>
<br>
Even though some will look green to you, they will give exp, and when they do, it's a big chunk.  Also, half of them will be blue at 49, especially the ones that spawn at the top of the tower.  Lev over with a sow or jboots, pull with Ice Comet, then run to the beach and back a bit.  One newb root and another comet, they are pasted.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you. <p><img src="http://kazzap.homestead.com/files/bar105.gif"><br>
Kazzap Allahandra 51st Wizard - Iskendar Woundtempest 52nd Warrior</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 5:38:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> Trying both now for a while I've determined that both are comprably 'easy' the giant arbors are occasionally green to me at 49 and drop in 2 ICs. Verdants in 3IC, ancients in 4IC and 1Rend(sometimes the 200damage stun).<br>
<br>
Loot is comparable. BW has a tendancy to give you a higher percentage chance at 'better' drops then CS. Where CS seems to have a bit better xp per avg kill.<br>
<br>
BW giants definatly don't like IC. Only Gorgul had IC hitting for less than 800 damage. I the realized that Gorgul was going to take a bit more than the mana I had remaining. That was pretty exciting.<br>
<br>
CS will be more interesting for me when I can quad them I'm sure. Anyone else recommend another zone where grouped or solo xp is good with comprable good loot?<br>
<br>
So far at 49 I've found:<br>
<br>
Dreadlands: loot crappy, mobs abundant, xp safe, xp ok<br>
CoM: loot rare but exceptional, mobs spawn regularly, hard to solo, hard to get a group, xp great<br>
Cobalt Scar: loot average, mobs available (not abundant), xp safe as snot, xp exceptional, solo or bust<br>
Burning Wood: loot average to good, xp ok, mobs abundant, xp safe<br>
<br>
Anywhere else I should check?<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 5:44:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> At 49 do the specs all come when you attack one or by then do they just come one at a time?  You may have already said but I like to make sure and hate to be dead. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenaddaranatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenaddar Anatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/01 5:47:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BW or CS at 49?</span><hr size=1> If you don't care about getting any, and I do mean any, loot. Check out Happ Dremblod in the LF zone. Shes a gnome caster (mage) with no faction hits. Once broken she spawns every 6 minutes on the dot, has a zone to Stormfont behind you and merchants nearby. <br>
<br>
My fear with CS is that its getting so busy with dr00ds who can't get a group and a Wizard or two all trying to quad everything in the zone so theres generally little to find there. Trust me on this one as I was one of those who first found CS a couple of days after SoV came out. It was heavenly then but now its been a pain with folks attempting to use the entire beach to quad. Leaving little room to do anything let alone see a mob up at all.<br>
<br>
If you need loot then BW is definitely the place to go. <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Lenaddar Anatar of Xev
(Lord of Wizardly Gifts from Tolkien) 56th Level Evoker

